Static Message Reader Driver
 Description

This project implements a simple Linux character device driver that always returns a static message:

Welcome to Kernel World!


whenever the device is read. It is useful as a beginner-level kernel driver project to understand the read() file operation and how user space interacts with kernel space.

Skills Covered

Implementing the read() file operation in a character driver

Returning a fixed response from the kernel to user space

Registering a basic character device driver (register_chrdev, unregister_chrdev)
